1
00:00:06,697 --> 00:00:28,120
The following is a talk given by the Venerable Mahasi Seada, Eka Mahapandita Usopana, given to his disciples on their induction into Vipassana meditation at Sasanayeta Meditation Center, Jango, Myanmar.

2
00:00:28,141 --> 00:00:35,590
Practical Vipassana Meditational Exercises The practice of Vipassana

3
00:00:35,823 --> 00:00:49,615
or inside meditation is the effort made by the meditator to understand correctly the nature of the psychophysical phenomena taking place in his own body.

4
00:00:50,616 --> 00:00:58,005
Physical phenomena are the things or objects which one clearly perceives around one.

5
00:00:58,865 --> 00:01:05,712
The whole of one's body that one clearly perceives constitutes a group of material qualities

6
00:01:06,012 --> 00:01:06,552
Rupa.

7
00:01:07,894 --> 00:01:15,266
Psychical or mental phenomena are acts of consciousness or awareness .

8
00:01:16,227 --> 00:01:29,587
These nama rupas are clearly perceived to be happening whenever they are seen, heard, smelled, tasted, touched or thought of.

9
00:01:30,888 --> 00:01:33,251
We must make ourselves aware of them

10
00:01:33,838 --> 00:01:53,180
observing them and noting thus, seeing, seeing, hearing, hearing, smelling, smelling, tasting, tasting, touching, touching, or thinking, thinking.

11
00:01:55,121 --> 00:02:03,710
Every time one sees, hears, smells, tastes, touches or thinks,

12
00:02:03,843 --> 00:02:06,466
one should make a note of the fact.

13
00:02:07,507 --> 00:02:14,677
But in the beginning of one's practice one cannot make a note of every one of these happenings.

14
00:02:15,618 --> 00:02:26,252
One should, therefore, begin with noting those happenings which are conspicuous and easily perceivable.

15
00:02:27,414 --> 00:02:33,562
With every act of breathing the abdomen rises and falls.

16
00:02:33,677 --> 00:02:37,162
Push movement is always evident.

17
00:02:38,144 --> 00:02:45,552
This is the material quality known as Vayodhatu, the element of motion.

18
00:02:46,493 --> 00:02:56,225
One should begin by noting this movement, which may be done by the mind intently observing the abdomen.

19
00:02:57,015 --> 00:03:24,306
You will find the abdomen rising when you breathe in and falling when you breathe out The rising should be noted mentally as rising and the falling as falling If the movement is not evident by just noting it mentally keep touching the abdomen with the palm of your hand Do not alter the manner of your breathing

20
00:03:24,724 --> 00:03:28,969
Neither slow it down nor make it faster.

21
00:03:28,990 --> 00:03:31,933
Do not breathe too vigorously either.

22
00:03:32,574 --> 00:03:37,600
You will tire if you change the manner of your breathing.

23
00:03:38,122 --> 00:03:45,211
Breathe steadily as usual and note the rising and falling of the abdomen as they occur.

24
00:03:45,991 --> 00:03:49,776
Note it mentally, not verbally.

25
00:03:49,796 --> 00:03:54,562
In Vipassana meditation, what you name or say doesn't matter.

26
00:03:55,167 --> 00:03:58,293
What really matters is to know or perceive.

27
00:03:59,114 --> 00:04:09,171
While noting the rising of the abdomen, do so from the beginning to the end of the movement, just as if you are seeing with your eyes.

28
00:04:09,913 --> 00:04:12,578
Do the same with the falling movement.

29
00:04:13,259 --> 00:04:15,723
Note the rising movement in such a way that

30
00:04:16,142 --> 00:04:20,550
Your awareness of it is concurrent with the movement itself.

31
00:04:21,250 --> 00:04:34,209
The movement and the mental awareness of it should coincide in the same way as a stone thrown hits the target, similarly with the falling movement.

32
00:04:35,552 --> 00:04:41,261
Your mind may wander elsewhere while you are noting the abdominal movement.

33
00:04:41,922 --> 00:04:45,406
This must also be noted by mentally saying,

34
00:04:45,860 --> 00:04:47,422
wandering, wandering.

35
00:04:48,343 --> 00:04:59,555
When this has been noted once or twice, the mind stops wandering, in which case you go back to noting the rising and falling of the abdomen.

36
00:05:00,516 --> 00:05:05,223
If the mind reaches somewhere, note as reaching, reaching.

37
00:05:06,103 --> 00:05:10,127
Then go back to the rising and falling of the abdomen.

38
00:05:10,968 --> 00:05:15,714
If you imagine meeting somebody, note as meeting,

39
00:05:15,896 --> 00:05:19,721
meeting, then back to the rising and falling.

40
00:05:20,502 --> 00:05:27,269
If you imagine meeting and talking to somebody, note as talking, talking.

41
00:05:29,673 --> 00:05:35,379
In short, whatever thought or reflection occurs should be noted.

42
00:05:36,300 --> 00:05:40,005
If you imagine, note as imagining.

43
00:05:40,685 --> 00:05:43,389
If you think, thinking.

44
00:05:43,410 --> 00:05:45,432
If you plan, planning.

45
00:05:45,850 --> 00:05:47,951
If you perceive, perceiving.

46
00:05:48,853 --> 00:05:51,014
If you reflect, reflecting.

47
00:05:51,595 --> 00:05:53,415
If you feel happy, happy.

48
00:05:53,456 --> 00:05:56,178
If you feel bored, bored.

49
00:05:56,798 --> 00:05:58,821
If you feel glad, glad.

50
00:05:59,380 --> 00:06:01,963
If you feel disheartened, disheartened.

51
00:06:02,923 --> 00:06:07,949
Noting all these acts of consciousness is called Sita Nupasana.

52
00:06:09,569 --> 00:06:15,654
Because we fail to note these acts of consciousness, we tend to identify them

53
00:06:15,922 --> 00:06:18,250
with a person or individual.

54
00:06:18,932 --> 00:06:27,220
We tend to think that it is I who is imagining, thinking, planning, knowing or perceiving.

55
00:06:27,901 --> 00:06:28,884
We think that

56
00:06:29,185 --> 00:06:34,853
There is a person who from childhood onwards has been living and thinking.

57
00:06:35,694 --> 00:06:39,201
Actually no such person exists.

58
00:06:40,103 --> 00:06:47,834
These are instead only those, only these continuing and successive acts of consciousness.

59
00:06:47,814 --> 00:06:54,523
That is why we have to know these acts of consciousness and know them for what they are.

60
00:06:55,184 --> 00:07:02,312
That is why we have to note each and every act of consciousness as it arises.

61
00:07:03,033 --> 00:07:06,117
When so noted, it tends to disappear.

62
00:07:06,716 --> 00:07:12,303
We then go back to noting the rising and falling of the active act.

63
00:07:14,257 --> 00:07:22,807
When you have sat meditating for long, sensations of stiffness and heat will arise in your body.

64
00:07:23,468 --> 00:07:25,850
These are to be noted carefully too.

65
00:07:26,651 --> 00:07:43,692
Similarly, with sensations of pain and tiredness, all of these sensations are Doka Viva Vedana, feeling of unsatisfactoriness, or noting them as Vedana Lubasana.

66
00:07:45,274 --> 00:08:03,266
Failure or omission to note these sensations makes you think, I am stiff, I am feeling hot, I am in pain, I was alright a moment ago, now I am uneasy with these unpleasant sensations.

67
00:08:04,208 --> 00:08:09,093
The identification of these sensations with the ego is mistaken.

68
00:08:09,714 --> 00:08:20,148
There is really no art involved, only a succession of one new unpleasant sensation after another.

69
00:08:20,187 --> 00:08:31,802
It is just like a continuous succession of new electrical impulses that light up electric lamps.

70
00:08:32,102 --> 00:08:42,850
Every time unpleasant contacts are encountered in the body, unpleasant sensations arise one after another.

71
00:08:43,511 --> 00:08:48,846
These sensations should be carefully and intently noted.

72
00:08:49,264 --> 00:08:55,715
whether they are sensations of stiffness, of heat, or of pain.

73
00:08:55,735 --> 00:09:07,815
In the beginning of the yogi's meditational practice, these sensations may tend to increase and lead to a desire to change his posture.

74
00:09:08,416 --> 00:09:11,019
His desire should be noted

75
00:09:11,000 --> 00:09:19,889
after which the yogi should go back to noting the sensation of stiffness, heat, etc.

76
00:09:22,092 --> 00:09:25,856
Patience leads to Nirvana, as the saying goes.

77
00:09:26,557 --> 00:09:31,102
This saying is most relevant in meditational effort.

78
00:09:32,083 --> 00:09:34,846
One must be patient in meditation.

79
00:09:35,384 --> 00:09:51,402
If one shifts or changes one's posture too often because one cannot be patient with the sensation of the stiffness or heat that arises, samadhi, good concentration, cannot develop.

80
00:09:52,057 --> 00:10:06,996
A samadhi cannot develop, insight cannot result, and there can be no attainment of mega, the path that leads to nirvana, phala, the fruit of that path, and nirvana.

81
00:10:08,499 --> 00:10:12,664
That is why patience is needed in meditation.

82
00:10:13,365 --> 00:10:14,486
It is patience

83
00:10:14,787 --> 00:10:26,003
mostly with unpleasant sensations in the body, like stiffness, sensations of heat and pain, and other sensations that are hard to bear.

84
00:10:26,744 --> 00:10:36,778
One should not immediately give up one's meditation on the appearance of such sensations and change one's meditational posture.

85
00:10:37,163 --> 00:10:47,076
One should go on patiently, just noting as stiffness, stiffness, or heart, heart.

86
00:10:47,096 --> 00:10:53,484
Moderate sensations of these kinds will disappear if one goes on noting them patiently.

87
00:10:54,264 --> 00:11:00,953
When concentration is good and strong, even intense sensations tend to disappear.

88
00:11:01,014 --> 00:11:06,039
One then reverts to noting the rising and falling

89
00:11:06,205 --> 00:11:08,388
of the abdomen.

90
00:11:08,408 --> 00:11:24,086
One will, of course, have to change one's posture if the sensations do not disappear, even after one has noted them for a long time, and if, on the other hand, they become unbearable.

91
00:11:25,369 --> 00:11:30,716
One should then begin noting as wishing to change, wishing to change.

92
00:11:31,395 --> 00:11:35,942
If the arm rises, notice rising, rising.

93
00:11:36,394 --> 00:11:40,298
If it moves, know that moving, moving.

94
00:11:41,200 --> 00:11:52,971
This change should be made gently and know that it is rising, rising, moving, moving, and touching, touching.

95
00:11:55,332 --> 00:11:59,116
If the body sways, swaying, swaying.

96
00:12:00,038 --> 00:12:04,221
If the foot rises, rising, rising.

97
00:12:04,241 --> 00:12:05,202
If it moves,

98
00:12:05,690 --> 00:12:07,052
moving, moving.

99
00:12:07,812 --> 00:12:10,777
If it drops, dropping, dropping.

100
00:12:11,879 --> 00:12:20,390
If there is no change but only static rest, go back to noting the rising and falling of the abdomen.

101
00:12:21,392 --> 00:12:32,528
There must be no intermission in between, only contiguity between a preceding act of noting and a succeeding one.

102
00:12:33,188 --> 00:12:35,072
Between a preceding samadhi

103
00:12:35,542 --> 00:12:44,153
state of concentration and succeeding one between the preceding act of intelligence and succeeding one.

104
00:12:45,053 --> 00:12:53,725
Only then will there be successive and ascending stages of maturity in the yogi state of intelligence.

105
00:12:53,745 --> 00:13:04,519
Megha and Pala Jnana, knowledge of the path and instruction, are attained only when there is this kind of gathering momentum.

106
00:13:05,004 --> 00:13:22,822
The meditative process is like that of producing fire by energetically and unremittingly rubbing two sticks of wood together so as to attain the necessary intensity of heat when the flame arises.

107
00:13:25,046 --> 00:13:32,092
In the same way, the noting in Vipassana meditation should be continual and unremitting.

108
00:13:32,461 --> 00:13:39,451
without any resting interval between acts of noting whatever phenomena may arise.

109
00:13:40,091 --> 00:13:59,700
For instance, if a sensation of itchiness intervenes and the yogi desires to stretch because it is hard to bear, both the sensations and the desire to get rid of it should be noted, without immediately getting rid of the sensations by stretching.

110
00:14:01,317 --> 00:14:15,673
If one goes on perseveringly noting thus, the itchiness may generally disappear, in which case one reverts to noting the rising and falling of the abdomen.

111
00:14:15,693 --> 00:14:23,602
If the itchiness does not in fact disappear, one has, of course, to eliminate it by stretching.

112
00:14:24,524 --> 00:14:29,129
But first, the desire to do so should be noted.

113
00:14:29,717 --> 00:14:51,147
All the movements involved in the process of eliminating this sensation should be noted, especially the touching, pulling and pushing and stretching movements with an eventual reversion to noting the rising and falling of the abdomen.

114
00:14:52,970 --> 00:14:59,538
Every time you make a change of posture, you begin with noting your intention

115
00:14:59,873 --> 00:15:14,190
desire to make the change and go on to noting every movement closely, such as rising from the sitting posture, raising the arm, moving and stretching it.

116
00:15:16,072 --> 00:15:21,278
You should make the change at the same time as noting the movements involved.

117
00:15:22,139 --> 00:15:25,222
As your body sways forward, note it.

118
00:15:25,793 --> 00:15:29,917
As you rise, the body becomes light and rises.

119
00:15:30,738 --> 00:15:37,245
Concentrating your mind on this, you should gently note as rising, rising.

120
00:15:38,346 --> 00:15:43,451
The yogi should behave as if he were a weak invalid.

121
00:15:44,212 --> 00:15:49,599
People in normal health rise easily and quickly or abruptly.

122
00:15:50,359 --> 00:15:55,664
Not so with feeble invalids who do so slowly and

123
00:15:55,847 --> 00:15:56,769
and gently.

124
00:15:57,369 --> 00:16:08,259
The same is the case with people suffering from backache who rise gently lest the back hurt and cause pain.

125
00:16:09,821 --> 00:16:12,423
So also with meditating yogis.

126
00:16:12,985 --> 00:16:19,070
They have to make their changes of posture gradually and gently.

127
00:16:19,090 --> 00:16:24,875
Only then will mindfulness, concentration and insight be good.

128
00:16:25,581 --> 00:16:30,528
Begin, therefore, with gentle and gradual movements.

129
00:16:31,210 --> 00:16:41,403
When rising, the yogi must do so gently like an invalid, at the same time noting as rising, rising.

130
00:16:42,063 --> 00:16:49,354
Not only this, though the eye sees, the yogi must act as if he does not see.

131
00:16:50,475 --> 00:16:55,302
Similarly, when the ear hears, while meditating,

132
00:16:55,736 --> 00:16:58,159
the yogi's concern is only to note.

133
00:16:58,760 --> 00:17:02,806
What he sees or hears are not his concern.

134
00:17:03,586 --> 00:17:15,722
So whatever strange or striking things he may see or hear, he must behave as if he does not see or hear them, merely noting carefully.

135
00:17:17,865 --> 00:17:22,992
When making bodily movements, the yogi should do so gradually

136
00:17:23,480 --> 00:17:36,877
as if he were a weak invalid, gently moving the arms and legs, bending or stretching them, bending down the head and bringing it up.

137
00:17:37,778 --> 00:17:41,042
All these movements should be made gently.

138
00:17:41,804 --> 00:17:51,175
When rising from the sitting posture, he should do so gradually, noting as rising, rising.

139
00:17:51,195 --> 00:17:52,557
When straightening up,

140
00:17:52,858 --> 00:17:56,823
standing, note as standing, standing.

141
00:17:58,163 --> 00:18:03,548
When looking here and there, note as looking, seeing.

142
00:18:05,651 --> 00:18:12,017
When walking, note the steps, whether they are taken with the right or the left foot.

143
00:18:12,917 --> 00:18:20,924
You must be aware of all the successive movements involved, from the raising of the foot to the dropping of it.

144
00:18:21,309 --> 00:18:28,180
Note each step taken, whether with the right foot or the left foot.

145
00:18:28,200 --> 00:18:31,845
This is the manner of noting when one walks fast.

146
00:18:34,067 --> 00:18:40,017
It will be enough if you note this when walking fast and walking some distance.

147
00:18:40,897 --> 00:18:50,912
When walking slowly or doing the Sankama walk, walking up and down, three movements should be noted in each step.

148
00:18:51,719 --> 00:18:58,087
when the foot is raised, when it is pushed forward, and when it is dropped.

149
00:18:58,970 --> 00:19:02,795
Begin with noting the raising and dropping movements.

150
00:19:03,817 --> 00:19:07,682
One must be properly aware of the raising of the foot.

151
00:19:08,503 --> 00:19:18,077
Similarly, when the foot is dropped, one should be properly aware of the heavy falling of the foot.

152
00:19:18,097 --> 00:19:21,522
One must walk noting as raising

153
00:19:21,740 --> 00:19:23,423
dropping with each step.

154
00:19:24,124 --> 00:19:28,652
This noting will become easier after about two days.

155
00:19:29,294 --> 00:19:39,471
Then go on to noting the three movements as described above, as raising, pushing forward, dropping.

156
00:19:40,192 --> 00:19:41,115
In the beginning,

157
00:19:41,415 --> 00:19:45,079
it will suffice to note one or two movements only.

158
00:19:45,640 --> 00:19:55,410
Thus, right step, left step, when walking fast, and raising, dropping, when walking slowly.

159
00:19:56,711 --> 00:20:05,140
When walking thus, you want to sit down, note as wanting to sit down, wanting to sit down.

160
00:20:06,020 --> 00:20:10,005
When actually sitting down, note concentratedly

161
00:20:10,441 --> 00:20:12,904
the heavy falling of your body.

162
00:20:15,548 --> 00:20:21,939
When you are seated, note the movements involved in arranging your legs and arms.

163
00:20:22,980 --> 00:20:34,338
When there are no such movements, but just a stillness, static rest of the body, note the rising and falling of the abdomen.

164
00:20:35,280 --> 00:20:46,133
While noting thus, and if stiffness of your beliefs and sensation of heat in any part of your body arise, go on to note them.

165
00:20:46,773 --> 00:20:50,057
Then back to rising, falling.

166
00:20:51,038 --> 00:21:01,308
While noting thus, if a desire to lie down arises, note it and the movements of your legs and arms as you lie down.

167
00:21:02,170 --> 00:21:03,751
The raising of the arm

168
00:21:04,103 --> 00:21:21,711
the moving of it, the resting of the elbow on the floor, the swaying of the body, the stretching of the legs, the listing of the body as one slowly prepares to lie down, all these movements should be noted.

169
00:21:23,933 --> 00:21:27,859
To note as you lie down thus is important.

170
00:21:27,880 --> 00:21:29,722
In the course of this movement,

171
00:21:30,007 --> 00:21:42,699
that is lying down, you can gain a distinctive knowledge, that is mega jnana and hlajnana, the knowledge of the path and its fruition.

172
00:21:43,460 --> 00:21:54,371
When samadhi, concentration, and jnana, insight, are strong, the distinctive knowledge can come at any moment.

173
00:21:55,672 --> 00:21:58,815
It can come in a single

174
00:21:59,182 --> 00:22:04,250
band of the arm or in a single stretch of the arm.

175
00:22:05,571 --> 00:22:10,920
Thus it was that the Venerable Ananda became an arhat.

176
00:22:12,342 --> 00:22:23,156
The Venerable Ananda was trying strenuously to attain arhatship overnight on the eve of the first Buddhist council.

177
00:22:23,176 --> 00:22:29,005
He was practicing the whole night the form of vipassana meditation known as

178
00:22:29,440 --> 00:22:49,557
Kayakta Sati, noting his steps, right and left, raising, pushing forward and dropping of the feet, noting, happening by happening, the mental desire to walk and the physical movement involved in walking.

179
00:22:50,438 --> 00:22:58,484
Although this went on till it was nearly dawn, he had not yet succeeded in attaining Arhatship.

180
00:22:59,663 --> 00:23:19,853
Realizing that he had practiced the walking meditation to excess and that in order to balance samadhi concentration and viriya effort, he should practice meditation in the lying posture for a while, he entered his chamber.

181
00:23:20,713 --> 00:23:24,660
He sat on the couch and then lay himself down.

182
00:23:25,480 --> 00:23:28,184
While doing so and noting

183
00:23:28,384 --> 00:23:33,980
Lying, lying, he attained arhatship in an instant.

184
00:23:36,527 --> 00:23:40,436
The venerable Ananda was only a satyapana.

185
00:23:41,159 --> 00:23:51,188
that is, a string winner, or one who has attained the first stage of the path to nirvana, before he thus lay himself down.

186
00:23:51,788 --> 00:24:06,921
From Sotapannakut he continued to meditate and reached Sakatagamikut, that is, the condition of the once returner, or one who has attained the second stage on the path.

187
00:24:07,942 --> 00:24:10,203
Anagamikut, that is,

188
00:24:10,420 --> 00:24:25,880
the state of the non-returner or one who has attained the third stage on the path, and arhatship, that is, the condition of the noble one who has attained the last stage on the path.

189
00:24:25,900 --> 00:24:32,348
Reaching these three successive stages of the higher path took only a little while.

190
00:24:33,109 --> 00:24:38,757
Just think of this example of the Venerable Ananda's attainment of arhatship.

191
00:24:39,412 --> 00:24:45,560
Such attainment can come at any moment and need not take long.

192
00:24:47,865 --> 00:24:52,571
That is why the yogi should note with diligence all the time.

193
00:24:53,173 --> 00:24:59,962
He should not relax in his noting, thinking this little lapse should not matter much.

194
00:25:00,983 --> 00:25:08,675
All movements involved in lying down and arranging the arms and legs should be carefully

195
00:25:09,009 --> 00:25:11,493
and unremittingly noted.

196
00:25:12,234 --> 00:25:21,429
If there is no movement but only stillness of the body, go back to noting the rising and falling of the abdomen.

197
00:25:22,190 --> 00:25:30,462
Even when it is getting late and time for sleep, the yogi should not go to sleep yet, dropping his noting.

198
00:25:31,243 --> 00:25:34,308
A really serious and energetic yogi

199
00:25:34,626 --> 00:25:40,674
should practice mindfulness as if he were foregoing his sleep altogether.

200
00:25:41,276 --> 00:25:45,561
He should go on meditating till he falls asleep.

201
00:25:46,823 --> 00:25:52,171
If the meditation is good and has the upper hand, he will not fall asleep.

202
00:25:53,112 --> 00:25:59,059
If, on the other hand, drowsiness has the upper hand, he will fall asleep.

203
00:26:00,461 --> 00:26:03,486
When he feels sleepy, he should note as

204
00:26:03,819 --> 00:26:24,106
sleepy, sleepy, if his eyelids droop, drooping, if they become heavy or leaden, heavy, if the eyes become smarting, smarting, noting thus the drowsiness may pass and the eyes become clear again.

205
00:26:24,166 --> 00:26:30,756
The yogi should then note as clear, clear,

206
00:26:31,192 --> 00:26:35,897
and go on to note the rising and falling of the Atman.

207
00:26:36,858 --> 00:26:47,191
However, perseveringly the yogi may go on meditating, if real drowsiness intervenes, he does fall asleep.

208
00:26:48,112 --> 00:26:50,835
It is not difficult to fall asleep.

209
00:26:51,395 --> 00:26:53,278
In fact, it is easy.

210
00:26:53,999 --> 00:27:00,185
If you meditate in the lying posture, you gradually become drowsy and eventually

211
00:27:00,537 --> 00:27:01,858
fall asleep.

212
00:27:02,459 --> 00:27:11,529
That is why the beginner in meditation should not meditate too much in the lying position.

213
00:27:12,671 --> 00:27:19,358
He should meditate much more in the sitting and walking postures of the body.

214
00:27:20,099 --> 00:27:26,847
But as it grows late and becomes time for sleep, he should meditate in the lying position.

215
00:27:27,267 --> 00:27:31,050
noting the rising and falling movements of the abdomen.

216
00:27:31,691 --> 00:27:36,195
He will then naturally, automatically fall asleep.

217
00:27:37,616 --> 00:27:42,141
The time he is asleep is the resting time for the yogi.

218
00:27:43,242 --> 00:27:50,348
But for the really serious yogi, he should limit his sleeping time to about four hours.

219
00:27:51,029 --> 00:27:55,114
This is the midnight time permitted by the Buddha.

220
00:27:55,246 --> 00:27:57,950
Four hours sleep is quite enough.

221
00:27:59,070 --> 00:28:08,344
If the beginner in meditation thinks that four hours sleep is not enough for health, he may extend it to five or six hours.

222
00:28:09,085 --> 00:28:12,410
Six hours sleep is clearly enough for health.

223
00:28:14,893 --> 00:28:19,599
When a yogi awakens, he should at once resume notating.

224
00:28:20,490 --> 00:28:31,566
The yogi who is really bent on attaining mega and khalanyana should rest from the meditational effort only when he is asleep.

225
00:28:32,448 --> 00:28:39,817
At other times, in his waking movements, he should be noting continually and without rest.

226
00:28:40,598 --> 00:28:49,991
That is why, as soon as he awakens, he should note the awakening state of his mind as Awakening, Awakening.

227
00:28:51,000 --> 00:28:59,788
If he cannot yet make himself aware of this he should begin noting the rising and falling of the abdomen.

228
00:28:59,808 --> 00:29:06,934
If he intends to get up from bed he should note as intending to get up intending to get up.

229
00:29:08,355 --> 00:29:16,703
He should then go on to note the changing movements he makes as he arranges his arms and legs.

230
00:29:17,684 --> 00:29:20,366
When he raises his head and rises

231
00:29:20,515 --> 00:29:23,297
note as rising, rising.

232
00:29:24,258 --> 00:29:29,563
When he is seated, note as sitting, sitting.

233
00:29:30,963 --> 00:29:38,891
If he makes any changing movements as he arranges his arms and legs, all of these movements should also be noted.

234
00:29:39,651 --> 00:29:49,559
If there are no such changes, but only a sitting quietly, he should revert to noting the rising and falling movements

235
00:29:49,826 --> 00:29:50,788
of the abdomen.

236
00:29:52,951 --> 00:30:00,439
One should also note when one washes one's face and when one takes a bath.

237
00:30:00,459 --> 00:30:08,488
As the movements involved in these acts are rather quick, as many of them should be noted as possible.

238
00:30:09,328 --> 00:30:16,576
There are then acts of dressing, of tidying up the bed, of opening and closing the door,

239
00:30:17,147 --> 00:30:22,115
All these should also be noted as closely as possible.

240
00:30:23,936 --> 00:30:32,788
When the yogi has his meal and looks at the meal table, he should notice looking, seeing, looking, seeing.

241
00:30:33,951 --> 00:30:43,864
When he extends his arm towards the food, touches it, collects and arranges it, handles it and brings it to the mouth,

242
00:30:44,214 --> 00:30:57,048
bends his hat and puts the morsel of food into his mouth, drops his arm and raises his head again, all these movements should be duly noted.

243
00:30:58,209 --> 00:31:03,054
This way of noting is in accordance with the Burmese way of taking a meal.

244
00:31:03,734 --> 00:31:11,843
Those who use fork and spoon or chopsticks should note the movements in an appropriate manner.

245
00:31:13,847 --> 00:31:18,914
When he chews the food, he should notice chewing, chewing.

246
00:31:19,836 --> 00:31:26,084
When he comes to know the taste of the food, he should notice knowing, knowing.

247
00:31:26,964 --> 00:31:35,636
As he relishes the food and swallows it, as the food goes down his throat, he should note all these happenings.

248
00:31:36,240 --> 00:31:43,087
This is how the yogi should note as he takes one morsel after another of his food.

249
00:31:43,808 --> 00:31:57,561
As he takes his soup, all the movements involved, such as extending of the arm, handling of the spoon, and scooping with it, and so on, all these should be noted.

250
00:31:58,282 --> 00:32:06,230
To note thus at new times is rather difficult, as there are so many things to observe and note.

251
00:32:06,835 --> 00:32:17,309
The beginning yogi is likely to miss several things which he should note, but he should resolve to note all.

252
00:32:17,329 --> 00:32:31,310
He cannot, of course, help it if he overlooks and misses some, but as his samadhi concentration becomes strong, he will be able to note closely all these happenings.

253
00:32:33,213 --> 00:32:34,715
Well, I have mentioned

254
00:32:35,000 --> 00:32:37,403
So many things for the yogi to note.

255
00:32:38,144 --> 00:32:42,548
But to summarize, there are only a few things to note.

256
00:32:43,170 --> 00:32:49,238
When walking fast, notice right step, left step.

257
00:32:49,258 --> 00:32:53,323
As raising, dropping, when walking slowly.

258
00:32:54,544 --> 00:33:01,292
When sitting quietly, just note the rising and falling of the abdomen.

259
00:33:01,313 --> 00:33:03,875
Note the same when you are lying.

260
00:33:04,395 --> 00:33:06,837
if there is nothing particular to note.

261
00:33:07,519 --> 00:33:19,611
While noting thus, and if the mind wanders, note the acts of consciousness that arise, then back to the rising and falling of the abdomen.

262
00:33:20,271 --> 00:33:33,525
Note also the sensation of stiffness, pain and ache and itchiness as they arise, then back to the rising and falling of the abdomen.

263
00:33:34,635 --> 00:33:53,296
Note also as they arrive the bending and stretching and moving of the limbs, bending and raising of the head, swaying and straightening of the body, then back to the rising and falling of the abdomen.

264
00:33:53,316 --> 00:34:00,063
As the yogi goes on noting thus, he will be able to note more and more of these happenings.

265
00:34:00,722 --> 00:34:04,186
In the beginning, as his mind wanders here and there,

266
00:34:04,588 --> 00:34:11,356
The yogi may miss noting many things, but he should not be disheartened.

267
00:34:12,255 --> 00:34:29,032
Every beginner in meditation encounters the same difficulty, but as he becomes more practiced, he becomes aware of every act of mind wandering till eventually the mind does not wander anymore.

268
00:34:29,934 --> 00:34:34,478
The mind is then riveted on the object of its attention

269
00:34:34,896 --> 00:34:48,898
the act of mindfulness becoming almost simultaneous with the object of its attention, such as the rising and falling of the abdomen.

270
00:34:48,918 --> 00:35:00,836
In other words, the rising of the abdomen becomes concurrent with the act of noting it and similarly with the falling of the abdomen.

271
00:35:02,521 --> 00:35:09,730
The physical object of attention and the mental act of noting are occurring as a pair.

272
00:35:10,690 --> 00:35:17,300
There is in this occurrence no person or individual involved.

273
00:35:17,320 --> 00:35:25,170
Only this physical object of attention and the mental act of noting occurring as a pair.

274
00:35:25,690 --> 00:35:32,659
the yogi will in time actually and personally experience these occurrences.

275
00:35:33,440 --> 00:35:47,579
While noting the rising and falling of the abdomen, he will come to distinguish the rising of the abdomen as physical phenomena and the mental act of noting of it as psychical phenomena.

276
00:35:48,481 --> 00:35:51,224
Similarly with the falling of the abdomen.

277
00:35:52,447 --> 00:35:53,047
Thus,

278
00:35:53,331 --> 00:36:03,626
the yogi will distinctly come to realize the simultaneous occurrence in pair of these psychophysical phenomena.

279
00:36:05,449 --> 00:36:23,135
Thus, with every act of noting, the yogi will come to know for himself clearly that there are only this material quality which is the object of awareness or attention and the mental quality

280
00:36:23,369 --> 00:36:25,012
That makes a note of it.

281
00:36:26,273 --> 00:36:36,931
This discriminating knowledge is called Nama Rupa Prithida Jnana, the beginning of the Vibhasana Jnana.

282
00:36:37,793 --> 00:36:43,043
It is important to gain this knowledge correctly.

283
00:36:43,063 --> 00:36:48,211
This will be succeeded, as the yogi goes on, by a knowledge that

284
00:36:48,800 --> 00:37:07,242
that distinguishes between the cause and its effect, which knowledge is called as the yogi goes on noting, he will see for himself that what arises passes away after a short while.

285
00:37:08,222 --> 00:37:17,253
Ordinary people assume that both the material and the mental phenomena go on lasting throughout life.

286
00:37:17,588 --> 00:37:21,614
that is, from youth to adulthood.

287
00:37:21,635 --> 00:37:23,818
In fact, that is not so.

288
00:37:25,041 --> 00:37:28,907
There is no phenomenon that lasts forever.

289
00:37:30,251 --> 00:37:40,608
All phenomena arise and pass away so rapidly that they do not last even for the twinkling of an eye.

290
00:37:41,568 --> 00:37:46,853
The yogi will come to know this for himself as he goes on noting.

291
00:37:47,614 --> 00:37:54,043
He will then become convinced of the impermanency of all such phenomena.

292
00:37:54,623 --> 00:37:59,909
Such conviction is called Anissa Nupasana Jnana.

293
00:38:00,730 --> 00:38:10,782
This knowledge will be succeeded by Dukha Nupasana Jnana, which realizes that all this

294
00:38:11,132 --> 00:38:14,376
impermanency is suffering.

295
00:38:14,396 --> 00:38:25,811
The yogi is also likely to encounter all kinds of hardship in his body, which is just an aggregate of sufferings.

296
00:38:26,692 --> 00:38:31,418
This is also dokha, nupasana, jnana.

297
00:38:32,259 --> 00:38:40,009
Next, the yogi will become convinced that all these psychophysical phenomena

298
00:38:40,411 --> 00:38:48,800
are occurring of their own accord, following nobody's will and subject to nobody's control.

299
00:38:49,599 --> 00:38:55,485
They constitute no individual or ego entity.

300
00:38:55,505 --> 00:39:00,371
This realization is anata-nupasana-jnana.

301
00:39:02,813 --> 00:39:08,679
When, as he goes on meditating, the yogi comes to realize firmly that

302
00:39:09,065 --> 00:39:14,690
All these phenomena are Anissa, Dota and Anatta.

303
00:39:14,710 --> 00:39:16,711
He will attain Nibbana.

304
00:39:17,452 --> 00:39:27,081
All the former Buddhas, Arhats and Aryas realized Nibbana following this very path.

305
00:39:27,101 --> 00:39:39,072
All meditating yogis should recognize that they themselves are now on this Satipatthana path in fulfillment of their

306
00:39:39,693 --> 00:39:57,099
wish for attainment of megayana, knowledge of the path, phalayana, knowledge of the fruition of the path, and nibbana, dhamma, and following the rabbining of their parmi, perfection of virtue.

307
00:39:57,860 --> 00:40:07,775
They should feel glad at this and at the prospect of experiencing the noble kind of samadhi, tranquility of mind,

308
00:40:08,009 --> 00:40:25,186
brought about by concentration and jnana, supramunding knowledge or wisdom, experienced by the Buddhas, Arhats and Aryas, and which they themselves have never experienced before.

309
00:40:26,849 --> 00:40:33,054
It will not be long before they will experience for themselves the mega-jnana,

310
00:40:33,456 --> 00:40:43,592
and Nibbana Dhamma experienced by the Buddhas, Arhats and Aryas.

311
00:40:43,612 --> 00:40:55,833
As a matter of fact, these may be experienced in the space of a month or of 20 or 15 days of the meditational practice.

312
00:40:55,853 --> 00:41:00,239
Those whose parami is exceptional

313
00:41:00,557 --> 00:41:04,862
may experience these dharmas even within seven days.

314
00:41:07,005 --> 00:41:22,684
The yogi should therefore rest content in the faith that he will attain these dharmas in the time specified above, that he will be freed of sakhyadity, ego-belief,

315
00:41:22,951 --> 00:41:32,706
and physicality, doubt or uncertainty, and saved from the danger of rebirth in the niver worlds.

316
00:41:34,047 --> 00:41:39,036
He should go on with his meditational practice in this faith.

317
00:41:40,855 --> 00:41:52,858
May you all be able to practice meditation well and quickly attain that nirvana which the Buddhas, Arhats and Aryas have experienced.

318
00:41:54,121 --> 00:41:58,510
Sadhu, Sadhu, Sadhu.
